io.github.zachohara.bukkit.common.persistence

Class PersistentKeyedMap<K,D extends java.io.Serializable>

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.github.zachohara.bukkit.common.persistence.PersistentObject
      • io.github.zachohara.bukkit.common.persistence.PersistentMap<java.lang.String,D>
        • io.github.zachohara.bukkit.common.persistence.PersistentKeyedMap<K,D>
  • Type Parameters:
    K - the key type for this map.
    D - the data type for this map. A data object must be able to be generated for any key object.
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    PersistentPlayerData

    public abstract class PersistentKeyedMap<K,D extends java.io.Serializable>
extends PersistentMap<java.lang.String,D>
    A PersistentKeyedMap object is responsible for loading and storing any given information that occurs in pairs as an external file, so that it remains persistent through server restarts. At its core, a PersistentKeyedMap object is essentially a PersistentMap with the map key being a String that is generated for any given key.
    Author:
    Zach Ohara

      • calculateDataValue

        public abstract D calculateDataValue(K key)
        Calculates and returns the relavant data value for the given key. Overriding this method allows sub-classes to have complete control over what data is stored for the specified key.
        Parameters:
        key - the key to calculate a data value for.
        Returns:
        the information for this map that is specific to the given key.

      • generateMapKey

        public java.lang.String generateMapKey(K key)
        Generate a key String that is specific to the given key object. This key will be used to store information in the map for the given object. Overriding this method allows sub-classes to have complete control over how the data is stored in the map, but the default implementation means that sub-classes are not required to generate their own map keys. By default, this method will simply use the toString() method of the key type.
        Parameters:
        key - the K key object to generate a map key for.
        Returns:
        the generated map key for the given data.
